#Text=Robert Aldridge
#Text=For other people , see Robert Aldridge ( disambiguation ) .
#Text=Robert Aldridge ( died 1616 ) was an English clergyman .
#Text=Life
#Text=Born at Burnham in Buckinghamshire , Robert Aldridge was educated at Eton and King 's College , Cambridge , where he was a Fellow from 1564 to 1567 . [ 1 ]
#Text=From 1576 to 1616 he was Rector of Wollaton 1576-1616 , and from 1 May 1578 to 1616 Vicar of St Mary 's Church , Nottingham .
#Text=He was the last Vicar of St Mary 's Nottingham to have the Crown as patron until 1973 .
#Text=It was in 1598 , during the incumbency of Robert Aldridge , that the Crown sold the patronage of St Mary 's to Sir Henry Pierrepont .

#Text=On 26 July 1592 , Thomas Clerke , of Nottingham , faced a charge in the Archdeaconry court , hee is presented for fightinge in the church with Robert Whitcombe . On 29 July he appeared and answered that upon a sondaie a fourtnight or three weekes sins in the church of saint Marie this respondent and others were ringinge of the belles and then and there this respondent did take a possie of flowers from Roberte Whitecombe the sextone , which Whitcombe demaunded them , and he denieinge to restore them the said sexton spake to him thus : thou shalt have my lief before thou have theim . and with that the sexton pulled this respondentes hat over his head and gave him a blowe on the eare with his hand . Whereuppon this jurate resisted him and others cominge upon theim at whose hand hee feared hurte , hee drawe his dagger and with it strake the sexton over the arme because he held him this jurate by the bosome and would not let him go .

#Text=And then the judge , accepting this confession , as he was and is bound , pronounced the said Clerke to have ipso facto incurred the sentence of excommunication by virtue of the statue in that case provided .
#Text=Then Mr Gymney , by virtue of order of the judge , absolved the said Thomas Clarke from the sentence of excommunication pronounced on account of his contempt of court .
#Text=John Darrell , of Queens ' College , Cambridge , was appointed by Robert Aldridge as curate .
#Text=Darrell already had a reputation for being involved in cases of exorcism .

#Text=Before long , he was involved again , this time in the case of William Sommers , who suffered from fits , or , as Darrell claimed , demonic possession . Darrell was accused of fraudulent exorcism and removed from his position by John Whitgift , Archbishop of Canterbury .

#Text=From the archdeaconry court records for 2 August 1606 , William Little Feere and Marmaduke Gregorie , churchwardens of St Mary 's Church , Nottingham were warned to see that the church of St. Mary , Nottingham was duly decorated in due form with the sentences of the Holy Scriptures before Michaelmas .
#Text=The churchwardens were also under pressure to repair the chancel , damaged by a storm in 1588 .
#Text=The repairs seem to still be outstanding as late as 1632 .
#Text=There are frequent entries in the Archdeaconry Records and include charges against the Vicar .
#Text=From the Churchwardens ' Presentment Bills for April 21 , 1612 .
#Text=St. Maries in Nott .
#Text=We the Churchwardens , here undernamed , do find that our chancell is in decay , but in whose defaulte we cannot lerne perfitly .
#Text=Item we present Mr. Robte .
#Text=Alderidg Clarke and our Vicar for selling a grave stone from the chancell .
#Text=Item we present Mr. Robte .
#Text=Alderidg , for burying nottoris fellons in the chancell .

#Text=On the same day in the Archdeaconry Court , a licence was granted to John Sherot to read prayers in St. Mary , Nottingham and to teach children the alphabet ( cum licentia ad decendum pueros Abcedarios ) .
#Text=The Register shows that Robert Aldridge was buried in the church , but his memorial has perished .
